            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "We probably shouldn't have both options, a single `target{s}`, e.g., of type `string|table` should be enough.\n\n(If we keep the name as `target` and just add the table override, it won't even break existing configs, as a treat!)",
            "commit_id": "f4702b3ebd346b283a2eadd7c2371355c3312c5a",
            "created_at": "2026-02-28T10:48:32Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -5284,9 +5284,10 @@ To enable the experimental UI (default opts shown): >lua\n     require('vim._core.ui2').enable({\n      enable = true, -- Whether to enable or disable the UI.\n      msg = { -- Options related to the message module.\n-       ---@type 'cmd'|'msg' Where to place regular messages, either in the\n+       ---@type 'cmd'|'msg' Default message target, either in the\n        ---cmdline or in a separate ephemeral message window.\n        target = 'cmd',\n+       targets = {}, ---@type table<string, 'cmd'|'msg'|'pager'> Kind specific message targets.\n        timeout = 4000, -- Time a message is visible in the message window.",
