        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> which tries to support both the old target and new targets name.\r\n\r\nThat's not what it's trying to do, although you're right that it does also end up doing that. Moving the default message target field (which is already undocumented here, but will stay necessary/useful) away from the `cfg` table wouldn't really change the code. But yes should probably move it to the messages module for clarity.",
